        "intervention": {
            "message": "CONTRAINDICATED: Concurrent use of rivaroxaban with strong combined CYP3A4 and P-gp inhibitors (ketoconazole, itraconazole, ritonavir, etc.) significantly increases rivaroxaban exposure and bleeding risk.",
            "recommendation": "Avoid co-administration. If antifungal therapy required, consider fluconazole (weak CYP3A4 inhibitor). If antiretroviral required, consult HIV specialist for DOAC-compatible regimen."
